---
import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Amritesh Shrivastava" description="About Amritesh Shrivastava - GRC Analyst and Security Engineer">
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper about">
			
			<div class="img-container">
				<img
					width="1553"
					height="873"
					src="/assets/profile.jpg"
					alt="Amritesh Shrivastava"
					class="profile-pic"
				/>
			</div>

			<Hero
				title="About Me"
				tagline="Part Auditor, Part Developer, Fully Committed to Security."
			>
			</Hero>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						I am a final-year <strong>Computer Engineering</strong> student at <strong>BMS College of Engineering, Bangalore</strong>, recently selected as a <strong>System Engineer at Infosys</strong>. 
					</p>
					<p>
						While most engineers focus solely on breaking code (Red Teaming) or fixing it (Blue Teaming), I found my passion in the structure that holds it all together: <strong>Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC)</strong>. However, I believe GRC shouldn't just be about spreadsheets and manual audits.
					</p>
					<p>
						My goal is to bridge the gap between <strong>Policy and Automation</strong>. By combining my background in C++ and Python development with my expertise as an <strong>ISO 27001:2022 Lead Auditor</strong>, I build tools that make compliance continuous, automated, and efficient.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Education</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p><strong>B.E. in Computer Science & Engineering</strong><br>
					BMS College of Engineering, Bangalore<br>
					<em style="color: var(--gray-400);">Expected Graduation: 2026</em></p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Philosophy</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						Security is not a checklist; it is a mindset. I advocate for <strong>"Compliance as Code,"</strong> ensuring that security standards like NIST CSF and CIS Benchmarks are integrated directly into the development pipeline, rather than checked retroactively.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>

		<ContactCTA />
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.about {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3.5rem;
	}

	.img-container {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	/* --- PROFILE PICTURE STYLES --- */
	.profile-pic {
		border-radius: 50%;
		aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
		object-fit: cover;
		width: 250px;
		height: 250px;
		border: 2px solid var(--neon-cyan);
		filter: grayscale(100%);
		transition: all 0.5s ease;
		display: block;
		box-shadow: none !important;
	}

	.profile-pic:hover {
		filter: grayscale(0%);
		transform: scale(1.05);
	}

	section {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--gray-200);
	}

	.section-title {
		grid-column-start: 1;
		font-size: var(--text-xl);
		color: var(--gray-0);
		font-family: var(--font-mono); /* Hacker Font */
	}

	.content {
		grid-column: 2 / 4;
	}

	.content :global(a) {
		text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
		text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
		transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
	}

	.content :global(a:hover),
	.content :global(a:focus) {
		text-decoration-color: currentColor;
	}

	@media (min-width: 50em) {
		.about {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
		}

		/* Both the Image Container and Hero need to be centered in the grid */
		.about > :global(:first-child),
		.about > :global(:nth-child(2)) {
			grid-column-start: 2;
		}

		section {
			display: contents;
			font-size: var(--text-lg);
		}
	}
</style>